<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1657" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1657">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/2327.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Clare</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Bluefields</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your telegram July 7. Sands badly wounded and was brought to this
                            Consulate about 1 a.m., 6th; consent given to keep him at the Consulate
                            a few days; delivered to the authorities yesterday and sent
                            hospital.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Clare</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>